{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ψόγος</b>, ὁ, <br /> (ψέγω) <b>blamable fault, blemish, flaw,</b> ἄνευ ψόγου τετυγμένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 5.2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>blame, censure,</b> ὀνείδεα καὶ ψ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Xenophanes Poeta Philosophus 11.2; σκοτεινὸς ψ. 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.61; μὴ τὸν ἀνθρώπειον αἰδεσθῇ ψόγον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 937, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 94: _plural_, ἐπὶ ψόγοισι δεννάσεις ἐμέ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 759 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ ψιλῶ ψόγους κλύειν conjecture for ψόφους in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 630 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in Comedy texts and Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 146, 895, etc.; τοῖς πέλας ψ. ἐπενεγκεῖν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.70, compare 2.45; ψ. φέρειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 182a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ψ. ἔχειν <b>to be blamed,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 823b; ψ. ἀμουσίας ὑφέξοντα [prev. author] “R.” 403c \">Refs</a>]: <i>plural</i>, ἐγκώμιά τε καὶ ψόγους ποιεῖν ἀλλήλοις <b>lampoons,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 829c, compare “Grg.” 483c, +others, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1448b27; τὸ.. κάλλος καὶ ψ. πολλῶν γέμει 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 703:—with _dative_, ἄλγος σοί, ψ. δὲ σῷ πατρί 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 987. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9798","accentedUnicode":"ψόγος","shortDef":"fault","mediumDef":"fault","stepGloss":"fault","stepTransliteration":"psogos","_step_Type":"word"}]}